SOURCE
http://www.washington.edu/news/2017/11/13/new-tool-quantifies-power-imbalance-between-female-and-male-characters-in-hollywood-movie-scripts/
AGENT
University of Washington.
GOAL
To discern how much power and agency film scripts give to each of their characters.
DATA
Nearly 800 movie scripts.
METHODS
Language analysis, specifically on the connotation frames of verbs.
RESULTS
It was discovered that there is a widespread gender bias in how male and female characters are portrayed. A searchable online database was created showing these biases.
COMMENTS
No comment.
